    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ec96387a1a8295b6fd6dffb68f80c352?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 6518696,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5043585,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5043585/guillaume-smet",
                "reputation": 10621,
                "display_name": "Guillaume Smet"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 23,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1687106401,
            "creation_date": 1562708810,
            "body": "<p>The warnings were a good indication.<\/p>\n<p>Your configuration is incorrect.<\/p>\n<p>It should be something like:<\/p>\n<pre><code>quarkus.http.cors=true\nquarkus.http.cors.origins=http://localhost:4200,http://localhost:9090\nquarkus.http.cors.headers=accept, authorization, content-type, x-requested-with\nquarkus.http.cors.methods=GET, OPTIONS\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>yaml config<\/p>\n<pre><code>quarkus:\n  http:\n    cors:\n      ~: true\n      origins: http://localhost:4200,http://localhost:9090\n      headers: accept, authorization, content-type, x-requested-with\n      methods: GET, OPTIONS, POST\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>with the <code>cors<\/code> prefix.<\/p>\n<p>We don't have proper documentation right now so better refer to <a href=\"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/extensions/undertow/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/undertow/runtime/filters/CORSConfig.java\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/extensions/undertow/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/undertow/runtime/filters/CORSConfig.java<\/a> .<\/p>\n<p>I opened <a href=\"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/3156\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/3156<\/a> to track the documentation issue.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 56960897,
            "question_id": 56959505,
            "last_edit_date": 1687106401
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/CAtv5.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 23021460,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 18146879,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/18146879/jos%c3%a9-junior",
                "reputation": 41,
                "display_name": "Jos&#233; Junior"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1644781925,
            "creation_date": 1644703789,
            "body": "<p>Try the following code, this worked for me.<\/p>\n<pre><code>&lt;code&gt;\n@Provider   \npublic class CorsFilter implements ContainerResponseFilter {\n  @Override\n  public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext, ContainerResponseContext responseContext) throws IOException {\n    responseContext.getHeaders().add(&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Origin&quot;, &quot;*&quot;);\n    responseContext.getHeaders().add(&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Credentials&quot;, &quot;true&quot;);\n    responseContext.getHeade`enter code here`rs().add(&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Headers&quot;, &quot;*&quot;);\n    responseContext.getHeaders().add(&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Methods&quot;, &quot;GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS, HEAD&quot;);\n    responseContext.getHeaders().add(&quot;Access-Control-Max-Age&quot;, &quot;100000&quot;);\n  }\n}\n&lt;/code&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 71096269,
            "question_id": 56959505,
            "last_edit_date": 1644781925
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/jYVAT.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 436296,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 823368,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/823368/andreas-panagiotidis",
                "reputation": 3092,
                "display_name": "Andreas Panagiotidis",
                "accept_rate": 0
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1726037672,
            "creation_date": 1726037672,
            "body": "<p>In Quarkus 3.X the following works for me in application.properties<\/p>\n<pre><code>quarkus.http.cors=true\nquarkus.http.cors.origins=*\nquarkus.http.cors.methods=GET, OPTIONS, HEAD, PUT, POST\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 78972403,
            "question_id": 56959505
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/qUdt3.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 6070986,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4739826,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4739826/dko",
                "reputation": 371,
                "display_name": "dko"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1726967542,
            "creation_date": 1708996329,
            "body": "<p>Adding <code>origin<\/code> to the list of headers accepted, fixed my issue.<\/p>\n<p>These were my config properties (file: <code>application.properties<\/code>):<\/p>\n<pre><code>quarkus.http.cors=true\nquarkus.http.cors.origins=/.*/\nquarkus.http.cors.headers=origin, accept, authorization, content-type, x-requested-with\nquarkus.http.cors.access-control-allow-credentials=true\nquarkus.http.cors.methods=GET,PUT,POST\nquarkus.tls.trust-all=true\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 78064650,
            "question_id": 56959505,
            "last_edit_date": 1726967542
        }
